Show container ids in list without --sync

The CONTAINER ID column was only populated when --sync queried the
backend; plain "rumpel list" always showed it blank. The daemon now
keeps an in-memory cache of backend container ids (docker container
id, kubernetes pod name), keyed by repo path and pod name, and serves
list requests from it. The cache is filled at launch (docker create
prints the id; the k8s pod name is the pod id we chose), refreshed by
the same per-host queries --sync runs, and entries are dropped when
the daemon deletes a container, so recreate never shows a stale id.

Because docker assigns ids at creation and nothing persists them,
a restarted daemon re-fetches ids on the first list: hosts not yet
reconciled this daemon lifetime are queried once, then marked warmed
so gone containers do not trigger a backend query on every list.
SSH hosts are only queried while connected, as with --sync. This
avoids a DB schema change, for which there is no migration story yet.
